HEADWORD: Despotical
<hw>Des*pot"ic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>despotiko`s</grk>:
cf. F. <ets>despotique</ets>.]</ety> <def>Having the character of, or
pertaining to, a despot; absolute in power; possessing and abusing
unlimited power; evincing despotism; tyrannical; arbitrary.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Des*pot"ic*al*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Des*pot"ic*al*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

